to buy you a midnight snack?

37
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:26,170
Ok. No problem.

38
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:27,940
- Let's go.
- Ok.

39
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:29,740
- It's ok.
- Good.

40
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,140
Let's go.

41
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:32,460
My sister is shy.

42
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,420
- It's your turn.
- Stop crying.

43
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:37,380
Stop crying. Wait.

44
00:02:37,380 --> 00:02:38,260
Grandma will play.

45
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,140
East.

46
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,370
Think of my daughter-in-law.

47
00:02:46,580 --> 00:02:48,220
She doesn't take care of her baby,

48
00:02:48,580 --> 00:02:49,500
but I have to.

49
00:02:50,060 --> 00:02:50,900
Instead,

50
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:51,940
she lives an easy life.

51
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:52,980
Come on. Stop crying.

52
00:02:52,980 --> 00:02:54,140
Don't cry anymore.

53
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:55,260
- Jiaxi...
- Stop crying.

54
00:02:55,260 --> 00:02:56,140
What's she doing?

55
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:58,260
Who knows?

56
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,700
Since she got laid off,

57
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,340
she's been mysterious.

58
00:03:04,140 --> 00:03:05,300
She often goes out at night.

59
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:06,580
I don't know why,

60
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,180
but she went out three times a week.

61
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:09,540
She's making money.

62
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:12,260
Making money in the night?

63
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,460
You don't know?

64
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:15,060
Never mind, then.

65
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:17,740
What do you mean?

66
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:20,140
Don't keep me guessing.

67
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,860
I hear she's singing for a living

68
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:25,180
in Crown Nightclub.

69
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:26,380
What?

70
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,460
We can't continue now.

71
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:36,780
♪In this big world, people go around♪

72
